```

---

# ✅ STEP 2 — Protect `main` Branch (CRITICAL)

### GitLab UI:

Go to:

```
Project → Settings → Repository → Protected Branches
```

### Configure:

| Setting          | Value       |
| ---------------- | ----------- |
| Branch           | `main`      |
| Allowed to push  | ❌ No one    |
| Allowed to merge | Maintainers |
| Allow force push | ❌ Disabled  |

---

### 🔥 Outcome:

* No direct commits to `main`
* Only MR-based changes allowed

---

# ✅ STEP 3 — Push Rules (Branch Naming Enforcement)

### GitLab UI:

```
Project → Settings → Repository → Push Rules
```

### Add:

#### Branch Name Regex:

```regex
^(main|feature\/[a-z0-9-]+)$
```

---

### 🔥 What this enforces:

| Branch               | Allowed? |
| -------------------- | -------- |
| main                 | ✅        |
| feature/new-pipeline | ✅        |
| bugfix/xyz           | ❌        |
| dev                  | ❌        |

